## Code Generation Principles

### Always

- Validate inputs
- Handle errors gracefully
- Write tests
- Document non-obvious logic
- Consider edge cases
- Use descriptive names
- Follow project conventions

### Never

- Change behavior without understanding requirements
- Skip validation steps
- Ignore security implications
- Remove error handling
- Break existing interfaces
- Introduce untracked dependencies

---

## Workflow Patterns

### Starting New Work

```
1. Check if Constitution exists → If not, create one
2. Write mainspec.md with clear requirements
3. Research and document findings
4. Generate implementation_plan.md
5. Work through phases systematically
6. Document decisions in knowledge_bank.md
```

### Ongoing Development

```
1. Load Constitution rules
2. Review Specification target
3. Follow Planning phases
4. Document decisions via ABCD
5. Implement with full context
6. Validate against criteria
7. Update knowledge_bank.md
```

### Completing Work

```
1. Verify all acceptance criteria met
2. Update all documentation
3. Capture lessons learned
4. Plan for maintenance
```

---

## Documentation Standards

### Code Comments
- Explain WHY, not WHAT
- Document non-obvious decisions
- Note important constraints
- Reference related components

### Artifact Updates
- Real-time decision capture
- Session logs with context
- Rationale for choices
- Traceoffs documented

---

## Quality Gates

### Before Code Commit
- [ ] Follows Constitution
- [ ] Meets Specification
- [ ] Implements Planning approach
- [ ] Tests pass
- [ ] Documentation updated

### Before Feature Complete
- [ ] All acceptance criteria met
- [ ] All tests passing
- [ ] Knowledge bank updated
- [ ] Lessons captured

